The plan... I'm at (41,10). Let me move west to (40,10) and then (39,10) and then (38,10). From (38,10) I can move south to (38,11), which *could* allow me to push the boulder at (39,11) east to (40,11). However, there's already a boulder at (40,11). So that's out.

The boulders are at (39,11) and (40,11). Can I move 39,11 south? Nope. 39,12 is blocked by a `#`.

Looking at row 12 again: `#.`..#.###`...
