My initial strategy was to push the boulder at (35,15) east. However, after careful observation of the adjacent squares, it appears I've backed myself into a corner (literally!). I can't push that boulder east because there's a wall. And I can't get behind the boulder I moved because there's a wall. I'm trapped! A moment of panic. This is bad!

Okay, let's step back. I need to rethink. I was so focused on that one boulder, I didn't see the bigger picture. I need to access the other boulders at (35,12) and (35,13).

I start to analyze the map. The rows with the other boulders show them in a space above me. I was originally at (37,15) and pushed the boulder. The initial map shows how I was positioned: I was `@` at (37,15). I moved the boulder to (35,15) and now it's boxed in. Damn!

